         <abstract id="aspace_f6b41298fad038ae9ffa733c6c98795c">Substantive letters and detailed diary entries document Buell's daily work as a missionary, her relationships with colleagues, and her views on events in China. Constance Buell was an educational missionary in north China from 1919 to 1951, serving under the American Board of Commissioners for Foreign Missions. She taught at Kobe College in Japan from 1952 to 1958.</abstract>
